I'm using Ivy with the new Ivy flag in the VSCode plugin, and I want to share some crucial issues:

### Invalid Directive

If I use a structural directive that doesn't exist, I don't get any error. Not in VSCode and not compile error:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20522870/106569136-d8857480-653c-11eb-8eb9-381887c6b777.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20522870/106569176-e2a77300-653c-11eb-8214-1138b314a270.png)

### Valid Directive

When I use the following custom directive:

```ts
@Directive({
  selector: '[appTest]'
})
export class TestDirective {
  @Input() appTest: 'foo' | 'bar';
  @Input() appTestType: boolean;

  constructor(private tpl: TemplateRef<any>, vcr: ViewContainerRef) { }
}
```

- I don't get autocomplete for the `appTest` input type:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20522870/106569431-2d28ef80-653d-11eb-9d00-0a6e15ee31b3.png)

- I don't get any error when passing the wrong type, even though it recognizes the type:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20522870/106569653-7e38e380-653d-11eb-85af-c521267e3f78.png)

- It doesn't recognizes additional inputs: ( not autocomplete or error )

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20522870/106569878-cb1cba00-653d-11eb-9a00-00c6fcc40ce3.png)

Angular version: ~11.1.1

# üêû Bug report

### Command (mark with an `x`)
- [ ] new
- [x] build
- [ ] serve

### Description

fileReplacements for non TypeScript (JavaScript) files doesn't work with ng build. ng serve correctly replaces all files defined in angular.json as stated in angular [docs](https://angular.io/guide/build#configure-target-specific-file-replacements) ```The main CLI configuration file, angular.json, contains a fileReplacements section in the configuration for each build target, which allows you to replace ```**any**``` file with a target-specific version of that file.```

This feature is critical for our project because some of our scss, html and assets files are different per configuration.

In #19717 have been discussion about this being expected behavior. I don't agree because ng serve works correctly and docs state this should work for **any** file.

If you don't agree, please fix docs and provide us alternative solution to replace files at compile time.

